---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy" description="How OperatorStack handles your data. Short version: we don't collect much, we don't sell anything, and we use privacy-friendly analytics.">

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:720px;">

      <span class="section-label">Legal</span>
      <h1 style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p style="color:var(--gray-400); font-size:0.9rem; margin-bottom:2rem;"><em>Last updated: March 2026</em></p>

      <div class="prose">

        <p>
          We run OperatorStack. Here's how this site handles your data,
          written in plain English because nobody reads legalese.
        </p>

        <h2>Analytics</h2>

        <p>
          This site uses <strong>Plausible Analytics</strong> — a privacy-friendly analytics
          tool that doesn't use cookies, doesn't collect personal data, and doesn't track
          you across sites. There's no cookie banner on this site because there are no
          cookies to consent to.
        </p>

        <p>
          Plausible tells me which pages get traffic, where visitors come from (Google,
          Twitter, direct), and what country they're in. That's it. No IP addresses stored.
          No fingerprinting. No advertising profiles. GDPR compliant by default.
        </p>

        <p>
          You can read <a href="https://plausible.io/data-policy">Plausible's data policy</a>
          if you want the technical details.
        </p>

        <h2>Email</h2>

        <p>
          If you subscribe to the OperatorStack email list — through the toolkit download
          or any signup form on this site — your email address is stored by
          <strong>ConvertKit</strong> (now Kit), our email service provider.
        </p>

        <p>
          What we store: your email address and the date you subscribed. That's it. We don't
          ask for your name, company, phone number, or anything else.
        </p>

        <p>
          Every email includes a one-click unsubscribe link. Click it and you're removed
          immediately. No "are you sure?" pages. No retention tricks. You're out.
        </p>

        <p>
          We will never sell, rent, or share your email address with anyone. Period.
        </p>

        <h2>Affiliate Links</h2>

        <p>
          This site contains affiliate links. When you click one and visit a vendor's
          site, that vendor may place tracking cookies in your browser to attribute the
          referral to us. These are <strong>third-party cookies that we don't control</strong>.
        </p>

        <p>
          Each vendor has its own cookie and privacy policy. We can't control what they
          track or how long their cookies last. If that concerns you, use your browser's
          private/incognito mode when clicking affiliate links, or clear cookies afterward.
        </p>

        <p>
          We disclose all affiliate relationships in every article that contains them and
          on our <a href="/affiliate-disclaimer">affiliate disclaimer</a> page.
        </p>

        <h2>We Never Sell Data</h2>

        <p>
          We don't sell your data. We don't rent it. We don't trade it. We don't share it
          with "partners" or "selected third parties" or whatever euphemism other sites use.
        </p>

        <p>
          The only data we have is your email address (if you subscribed) and anonymous
          page-view analytics. Neither is for sale. Ever.
        </p>

        <h2>Questions</h2>

        <p>
          If you have questions about this privacy policy, reply to any email from us.
          That goes directly to me.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing Law</h2>

        <p>
          This privacy policy is governed by the laws of the State of Illinois,
          United States.
        </p>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
